    <main class="section__container">
        <h1 class="section__header">BMI Calculator</h1>
        <p class="section__description">Calculate your Body Mass Index (BMI) to get an idea of your body composition.</p>
        
        <div class="bmi-calculator">
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="weight">Weight (kg):</label>
                <input type="number" id="weight" placeholder="Enter weight in kg" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="height">Height (cm):</label>
                <input type="number" id="height" placeholder="Enter height in cm" />
            </div>
            <button onclick="calculateBMI()" class="btn">Calculate BMI</button>
            <div id="result" class="result"></div>
        </div>

        <section class="bmi-info">
            <h2>Understanding BMI</h2>
            <p>BMI is a simple way to gauge whether you're at a healthy weight. Here's what the numbers mean:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Below 18.5:</strong> Underweight</li>
                <li><strong>18.5 - 24.9:</strong> Normal weight</li>
                <li><strong>25 - 29.9:</strong> Overweight</li>
                <li><strong>30 or greater:</strong> Obese</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Remember, BMI is just one measure of health. Consult with a healthcare professional for a comprehensive health assessment.</p>
        </section>
